<title>USA: Novell wins $200,000 in patent case.</title>
<headline>Novell wins $200,000 in patent case.</headline>
<dateline>PROVO, Utah 1997-06-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>Novell Inc said Tuesday that it has won summary judgment in its case against RTI of Killeen, Texas, granting Novell's request for $200,000 in statutory damages as well as attorney's fees.</p>
<p>Novell said the judgment was granted in the U.S. District Court for the Western District of Texas in Waco.</p>
<p>The company said that in November 1994, it sued RTI for allegedly illegally manufacturing and selling counterfeit software.</p>
<p>RTI filed for bankruptcy in August 1995, but Novell said it prevailed in its claim that intentional torts, such as copyright infringement, cannot be discharged in bankruptcy.</p>
